column5: I live in Barrie, and all i really know for fishing spots that you don't need a boat for are end of Big Bay Point, the Gov. pier on 3rd or 4th side of Oro, and out in Angus. I would love to know how to get into Little Lake without going into the trailer park or something like that style of fishing.  Thanks for the help

Aw man i'd realy like to help you out here  , i live not that far from there , have to be careful how i explain this ,you can try going to C hill then head west til it heads north but you go south to the dead end , you might be able to walk from there in , its the only spot that i know of that you could try ............ good luck
I should be careful as well,but I believe the gates are locked shut
